<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 06 at 6:17AM EDT  by NWS Chicago</headline>
<description>...Patchy Dense Ground Fog Early This Morning...
Patchy dense ground fog will result in locally reduced
visibilities, likely down to a quarter mile or less in spots. Due
to the patchy nature of the fog, travelers this morning should
exercise caution and be prepared for rapidly changing visibility.
Fog will quickly dissipate by around 8 am. If you encounter fog
traveling this morning, use low beams and increase following
distance.</description>
